Marzin: Second highest use of Dots.  However, the Symbol lasts a lot longer so not as many Dots will be use.<br><br>Level 58 - 59: Naltron's Mark: IF (and that is a BIG if) the Cleric has this spell, it's absolute bliss.  1 Dot and the group is covered for a good period of time.  For exping, Naltron's Mark is the way to go.  It covers everyone with one cast and only uses a single Dot.  However, the spell is rare and not all Clerics have access to it.<br><br>Level 60: Aegolism/Blessing of Aegolism: Low use of Dots if there are no deaths.  Aegolism lasts awhile and only uses a single Dot.  Blessing of Aegolism is one of the all time greatest spells invented.  I cast it for 4 Dots and and the entire group is covered (if no deaths) for a good 2.5 hours.  For exping, it doesn't take much to cover the costs.  Either spell, Dot usage is minimal compared to earlier levels requiring Symbols refreshed every half hour or so.<br><br>Anyway these are just my random thoughts and observations. <p><A Href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6975" Style="text-decoration: none">Quistil Angelwatch</a><br>High Priest in the service to the Great Mother Tunare <br>Islington Angelwatch<br>Cavalier of 53 seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulukariatrueheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lukaria Trueheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/20/02 7:33:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much compensation do clerics require?</span><hr size=1> IMO you want to give enough to cover the cleric's peridot cost THEN split the cash.  If an enchanter is there using that spell that takes a peridot (for the life of me I cannot remember the name at this time..) they should also be compensated for the cost.  <br><br>This way, all the costs are covered, then the cash/gems are split equally so that everyone comes out equally ahead.<br><br>If you only give the cleric enough to cover the cost of the peridots, they did not make any extra cash, whereas the others in the group did.<br><br>If a group wants to be generous and give me all the cash loot/cash gems - thats fine with me.  I always go broke as I don't usually ask for extra cash - atm I only have 200 pp in the bank (gotta go to OS I spose).  But thats my fault for not insisting on the dots costs being covered.  I know clerics that will leave a group if their costs are not covered.  I won't as long as the exp is good and no one is being greedy though.<br><br>And also - /agree Hop - it depends where you are on what is dropped and hence - the cash loot amount.<br><br>Quest gems/spells should go to the classes that can use them - if no one can, then random to group for guild/friend usage or selling.<br><br>Just my opinion though.<br> <br><br><br><br> <p>Lukaria Trueheart<BR>55th Templar<BR>Phoenix Crusaders<BR><BR><BR>/blonde <BR><BR>This is my excuse for every stupid thing I do, say, fail to do or say, succeed at saying or doing, intend to say or do, and all things I actually do and say but didn't mean to do or say.<BR><BR>What do you mean I'm not blonde? </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvendrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vendrix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1258<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/20/02 7:58:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much compensation do clerics require?</span><hr size=1> Fortunately for me, I discovered the bountiful gem harvest, known as the Necrosis spawn, very early on in Kunark. I did roughly 70% of my time between 53-60 at that one spot. Over the course of those two or so months I raked in roughly 25K plat in gems alone, I took them all!<br><br>Now, right off I sound like a Scrooge, miser, whatever. It sounds as if I took all the cash and put my guild/group mates in the soup line. Maybe if you take a snapshot in time, it might seem like that was the case. When I hit 60 there was no alternate exp to continue on with. You hit 60, then you helped friends hit 60 and then you raided all the time, or played a twink. The moment I filled my bar in level 60 was the moment I ceased to have an income. For the rest of my days I lived off that 25K. I took money when people offered and there was the guild fund, but at no point in time, in my entire EQ life, did I have enough to afford to buy anything. If I was still playing Everquest I can say, with utmost certainty, that I would not own a mule, let alone a horse.<br><br>Class to class comparison across the board, I would wager that Clerics are the poorest overall. They are the only class that, if played correctly(meaning you buff when you're supposed to), has a constant outward flow of cash that goes far beyond food/water.<br><br>So yes, you may get in a group with Cleric X who wants all the gems that are dropping and he may seem greedy, but… That exp group is costing you nothing, zero. His next 10 groups may be in a zone where gems don’t drop, NBG items go to other people and he’s still shelling out cash while those same 10 groups cost others – nothing. <p><b>Vendrix</b><br><a href=http://www.dakor.net><font size=2>Da</a><a href=http://www.fatsex.com/tour>`</a><a href=http://www.dakor.net>Kor</font></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezb